### Order API Requests
# This file contains HTTP requests for testing Order endpoints.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api/v1
@authToken = YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE
@orderId = 1
@orderItemId = 1

### 1. Get All Orders
# Returns all orders with customers, items, discounts, and transactions.
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

# Expected Response: 200 OK
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "Orders fetched successfully",
#   "data": [
#     {
#       "id": 1,
#       "orderNumber": "ORD-A1B2C3D4",
#       "status": "completed",
#       "discountedTotalPrice": 90.00,
#       "customer": { ... },
#       "items": [...],
#       "transactions": [...]
#     }
#   ]
# }

### 2. Get Single Order
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/{{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

# Expected Response: 200 OK
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "Order fetched successfully",
#   "data": { ... }
# }

### 3a. Create Order (With Discount & Partial Fulfillment)
# Creates a new order. Stock is automatically deducted from inventory.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "customerId": 1,
    "paymentMethod": "cash",
    "discountCode": "SAVE10",
    "notes": "Deliver to the front desk",
    "items": [
        {
            "productId": 1,
            "quantity": 100,
            "fulfilledQuantity": 40
        }
    ]
}

# Expected Response: 201 Created
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "Order created successfully",
#   "data": {
#     "id": 5,
#     "orderNumber": "ORD-E5F6G7H8",
#     "status": "partially_fulfilled",
#     "discountAmount": 10.00,
#     "discountedTotalPrice": 90.00,
#     "items": [...]
#   }
# }

### 3b. Create Order (No Discount, Full Fulfillment)
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "customerId": 1,
    "paymentMethod": "momo",
    "items": [
        {
            "productId": 2,
            "quantity": 5,
            "fulfilledQuantity": 5
        }
    ]
}

# Expected Response: 201 Created (Status: "completed")

### 4. Fulfill Order Item (Partial or Full)
# Use this to track when a customer takes their remaining items.
# Quantity to fulfill must be <= remaining unfulfilled quantity.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/item/{{orderItemId}}/fulfill
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "quantity": 30
}

# Expected Response: 200 OK
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "Successfully fulfilled 30 units",
#   "data": {
#     "id": 1,
#     "fulfilledQuantity": 70,
#     "fulfillmentStatus": "partial"
#   }
# }

### 5. Cancel Order
# Reverses inventory and cancels transactions.
# Only allowed for CEO/Manager roles.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/{{orderId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

# Expected Response: 200 OK
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "Order cancelled and stock returned successfully"
# }
